<DOC><DOCNO> AP880606-0288 </DOCNO><FILEID>AP-NR-06-06-88 1910EDT</FILEID><FIRST>r f AM-Rich'sCuts     06-06 0169</FIRST><SECOND>AM-Rich's Cuts,0179</SECOND><HEAD>Chain Taken Over By Campeau Axes 250</HEAD><DATELINE>ATLANTA (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   Rich's department stores, a unit of FederatedDepartment Stores Inc., announced Monday it is laying off 250employees as part of Campeau Corp.'s streamlining of Federated.   Most of the employees being laid off are management andsupervisory personnel, Rich's announced.   ``No salespeople are being reduced,'' the company said.   Rich's, with 20 stores, currently employs about 9,000 workers.About 80 percent of the firings will be in the central organization,with 20 percent in the company's stores, located in Georgia, Alabamaand South Carolina, the announcement said.   Rich's is the third store division of Federated to announceemployee cuts since the Toronto-based Campeau took control of thechain in a $6.6 million buyout.   Ohio-based Lazarus stores have dismissed 1,200 employees, andanother 320 have been laid off at Miami-based Burdine's.   In addition, 92 of 530 employees at Federated's Cincinnatiheadquarters were let go.   No additional cutbacks were expected at the Atlanta-based Rich's,spokeswoman Anne Berg said.</TEXT></DOC>